commit.message:
README: emphasize no xorg required (#677)

* README: emphasize no xorg required

This is precisely what makes omxplayer unique and valuable.

* README: revise intro for accuracy

Also: further target beginners by providing links to explain acronyms.

Disable subtitles on Pi4 or if KMS is enabled

They also use VG rendering which isn't available if either
of those conditions is true.

Fix check for KMS/FKMS

sscanf returns the number of elements read, and the check
wasn't inserting any parameters into the format string.

If  no parameter is provided, do a strcmp instead.
omxplayer: Disable osd on pi4 or when fkms is enabled
makefile: Remove some questionable compiler flags
Fix FFmpeg 4.0 causes omxplayer to hang-up at the end. (#637)
Fix key(board) input not working after system update. (#649)
redirect which stderror to /dev/null

use "type -p" instead of "which"

On Raspberry Pi's without a desktop, the following non-fatal error messages appear when starting omxplayer:

```
/usr/bin/omxplayer: line 25: which: command not found
/usr/bin/omxplayer: line 26: which: command not found
/usr/bin/omxplayer: line 27: which: command not found
```

These errors are a result of the `which` command failing to find the fbset, xset, and xrefresh binaries, which are only present when running xserver.

One way to avoid seeing the error message is to use `type -p` rather than `which`. Alternatively one could just pipe stderror to /dev/null. I chose the former, but either way works fine.

fix GPL mailing address

This change updates the gpl mailing address to the current one [1], which fixes the following warning from rpmlint:
```
omxplayer.armv7hl: W: spurious-executable-perm /usr/share/man/man1/omxplayer.1.gz
```
[1] https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.en.html
omxplayer: No longer need to delay sending EOS

Pass SubmitEOS message through decode queue

So, the problem is that SubmitEOS is called when demuxer reaches end of file, but not all the encoded frames have been submitted to decoder.

m_packets may contain dozens of encoded frames of data at the point SubmitEOS is called. We want those to all be submitted to decoder before the SubmitEOS is called.

Use new OMX_DISPLAY_ALPHA_FLAGS_DISCARD_LOWER_LAYERS flag to avoid having to blank screen

Note: Requires updated firmware
OMXVideo: Fix indentation
Added DBUS SetLayer command to change the display layer while playing.
Added dbus OpenUri command to change the video source URI. As proposed on Github by popcornmix/omxplayer issue #528.
changes to ffmpeg 4 (#634)

Resample embedded samplerate to rate nearest of the target device. (#613)

Fix issue #612 mp3 files play at 2x or 4x the speed.
Makefile: Reinstate install target

fixes for building in Stretch (#573)

* fixes for building in Stretch

* another required change or the build fails

* tidy up dependency

* use 4 threads to compile and save time

* use CPU core count for threads instead of hard-coding it to 4

* removed wrong -j flag for making ffmpeg

* multi core compiling for ffmpeg

* makefile: Remove broken cross compile support

* no longer patch Makefiles before compiling
Updated README docs to be clear that Stop and Quit have the same effect
Fix a trivial cnp error
bugfix: Command "getsource" must exit with a non-zero code on error

fix for issue #521

Neither Subtitles nor OSD text messages are shown in full screen.

Subtitle scaling with video size (#519)

Subtitle scaling with video size

With this change subtitles and status texts are resized to scale and moved to follow video, when omxplayer is started with the --win option or is resized via dbus setvideopos command.
Previous behavior was: when video was resized, subtitles stayed the same size, as if the video was still in fullscreen.

This is particularly useful in windowed GUI omxplayer wrappers such as KenT2/tboplayer
Fix bug where cookie and user-agent values aren't set when --live flag is used.

OMXPlayer: Fix bug where audio timestamps fail to update

This causes issues with out of sync audio after packet loss with live tv
See: http://forum.kodi.tv/showthread.php?tid=269814&pid=2412025

Merge pull request #485 from T-X/alsa-dep-fix

Add libasound2-dev as required package
